Once it bonds with humans,

289
00:14:14,320 --> 00:14:16,279
it'll be hard to release it later.

290
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:20,120
You all head back first.

291
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:21,759
I'll stay tonight to observe.

292
00:14:44,759 --> 00:14:45,320
Hello?

293
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:46,639
Hello, Nana?

294
00:14:47,559 --> 00:14:49,360
Is Smiley doing better today?

295
00:14:49,879 --> 00:14:50,799
Not really.

296
00:14:50,919 --> 00:14:52,360
Still under observation.

297
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,399
Are you still at the rescue center?

298
00:14:58,919 --> 00:14:59,480
Okay.

299
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:25,399
It's my first time here at night.

300
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:27,240
It really looks different.

301
00:15:28,039 --> 00:15:28,559
Yes.

302
00:15:28,919 --> 00:15:31,120
I also love walking here at night.

303
00:15:31,519 --> 00:15:33,039
There aren't many people in the park at night.

304
00:15:33,039 --> 00:15:34,399
Look up and it's all stars.

305
00:15:36,480 --> 00:15:37,000
Come.

306
00:15:38,120 --> 00:15:38,600
Eat.

307
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:43,879
I swear I gain weight every time I see you.

308
00:15:44,120 --> 00:15:45,759
But I really have no appetite today.

309
00:15:46,080 --> 00:15:47,120
I'll eat it tomorrow.

310
00:15:50,039 --> 00:15:51,000
Have some plum juice.

311
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:52,759
Okay.

312
00:15:54,759 --> 00:15:56,039
Add ice if you want.

313
00:15:59,279 --> 00:16:00,039
It's delicious.

314
00:16:00,039 --> 00:16:00,639
Which place is it from?

315
00:16:02,080 --> 00:16:02,799
Hong Shiliu

316
00:16:04,120 --> 00:16:05,039
Homemade.

317
00:16:06,799 --> 00:16:07,399
If you like it,

318
00:16:07,399 --> 00:16:08,679
tell me in advance next time.

319
00:16:08,720 --> 00:16:09,360
I'll make it for you.

320
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:23,919
Smiley is just like you.

321
00:16:25,159 --> 00:16:26,240
When it's upset,

322
00:16:26,399 --> 00:16:27,559
it can't eat.

323
00:16:31,559 --> 00:16:33,159
Smiley shows signs of depression.

324
00:16:33,639 --> 00:16:34,360
That serious?

325
00:16:36,159 --> 00:16:37,559
Actually, many people don't know

326
00:16:37,799 --> 00:16:39,279
animals have emotions too.

327
00:16:39,919 --> 00:16:41,240
Like OCD,

328
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:42,159
anxiety,

329
00:16:42,159 --> 00:16:42,919
phobias,

330
00:16:42,919 --> 00:16:44,039
PTSD,

331
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:45,919
all can happen to them.

332
00:16:46,279 --> 00:16:48,679
Worse, they can develop stereotypes

333
00:16:48,879 --> 00:16:50,639
and somatization and other behaviors.

334
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:03,919
I read a news story before

335
00:17:04,119 --> 00:17:06,119
about a tiger in a zoo

336
00:17:06,640 --> 00:17:08,640
that lost its cub.

337
00:17:08,920 --> 00:17:09,960
It became depressed.

338
00:17:10,240 --> 00:17:12,160
Then the zookeepers

339
00:17:12,160 --> 00:17:15,039
dressed a piglet in tiger skin.

340
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:17,640
In the end, the tiger treated the piglet

341
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:19,119
as its own cub.

342
00:17:20,599 --> 00:17:22,920
If Smiley gets used to my scent,

343
00:17:23,519 --> 00:17:26,440
should I wear a bear suit too?

344
00:17:26,799 --> 00:17:27,960
I'll be its foster dad.

345
00:17:28,359 --> 00:17:28,920
Would that work?

346
00:17:37,559 --> 00:17:39,640
I'm really happy tonight.

347
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:50,519
Farman told me

348
00:17:51,880 --> 00:17:53,039
the family's attitude

349
00:17:53,119 --> 00:17:54,759
affects the patient's mood.

350
00:17:56,119 --> 00:17:58,160
He said if I'm positive and optimistic,

351
00:17:58,720 --> 00:18:00,279
my mom will feel better too.

352
00:18:00,960 --> 00:18:02,119
Then there's still hope.

353
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:06,920
Same goes for you.

354
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:10,640
Let's go.

355
00:18:11,039 --> 00:18:11,920
I'll take you somewhere.

356
00:18:13,599 --> 00:18:15,279
Yueyue probably told you already.

357
00:18:15,519 --> 00:18:17,680
She wants you to be Smiley's foster dad.

358
00:18:18,559 --> 00:18:19,519
But I didn't agree.

359
00:18:22,160 --> 00:18:23,519
Before my mom passed away,

360
00:18:24,920 --> 00:18:26,640
she told my dad

361
00:18:27,799 --> 00:18:29,680
not to buy shoes with laces.

362
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:32,799
Nana couldn't tie her laces yet.

363
00:18:35,400 --> 00:18:36,480
They all say

364
00:18:37,279 --> 00:18:39,480
time makes you forget everything.

365
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:41,759
But I don't think that's true.

366
00:18:43,680 --> 00:18:46,039
Time just stores some memories away.

367
00:18:47,519 --> 00:18:48,960
Then, when you least expect it,

368
00:18:48,960 --> 00:18:49,960
they suddenly resurface.

369
00:18:53,279 --> 00:18:56,680
Like when I see a young mom

370
00:18:56,799 --> 00:18:58,880
tying her daughter's shoelaces.

371
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:03,319
When I heard Mama Aysha was ill,

372
00:19:05,240 --> 00:19:06,920
my heart still aches.

373
00:19:10,759 --> 00:19:11,720
Don't laugh at me,

374
00:19:14,039 --> 00:19:15,240
but lately, several times

375
00:19:17,400 --> 00:19:19,160
I've woken up suddenly from sleep.

376
00:19:20,519 --> 00:19:22,960
I sneak to my mom's window

377
00:19:24,519 --> 00:19:25,359
and see her

378
00:19:26,319 --> 00:19:27,759
before I can relax.

379
00:19:30,519 --> 00:19:31,880
That's why I don't want you

380
00:19:31,880 --> 00:19:33,599
to be Smiley's foster dad.

381
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:38,880
Even if you become Smiley's foster dad,

382
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:42,000
I might not be able to save it.

383
00:19:42,960 --> 00:19:44,480
Even if I do save it,

384
00:19:45,240 --> 00:19:46,839
we still have to try to release it.

385
00:19:48,279 --> 00:19:49,839
So, at some point,

386
00:19:50,279 --> 00:19:51,799
you'll lose it anyway.

387
00:19:54,319 --> 00:19:55,880
Of course I know the ending

388
00:19:55,880 --> 00:19:56,799
will be

389
00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:57,880
separation.

390
00:20:00,599 --> 00:20:02,160
But the process is beautiful,

391
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:05,119
irreplaceable.

392
00:20:06,519 --> 00:20:07,519
I want to give it a try.

393
00:20:08,319 --> 00:20:09,000
Nana

394
00:20:10,519 --> 00:20:11,759
Seeing it like this now,

395
00:20:11,759 --> 00:20:12,920
I really want to try.

396
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:14,559
Even if there's only a tiny chance,

397
00:20:16,079 --> 00:20:17,039
I want to try.

398
00:20:18,279 --> 00:20:18,839
Is that okay?

399
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:29,200
You're stronger than I thought.

400
00:20:40,039 --> 00:20:40,599
Thank you.

401
00:20:40,680 --> 00:20:41,240
Take care.

402
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:42,000
Okay, thanks.

403
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:43,839
Take care.

404
00:20:44,519 --> 00:20:45,119
Come on, come on.

405
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:46,000
Give it to me, Ming Liang.

406
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:46,599
Go ahead, go on.

407
00:20:46,599 --> 00:20:47,519
No rush, I'll finish it.

408
00:20:47,880 --> 00:20:48,519
Don't worry.

409
00:20:48,519 --> 00:20:49,759
You still don't trust me with it?

410
00:20:50,240 --> 00:20:50,720
Alright.

411
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:01,640
Aisha.

412
00:21:02,559 --> 00:21:03,799
Do you know Ming Liang

413
00:21:03,799 --> 00:21:05,519
why he's in such a hurry?

414
00:21:05,559 --> 00:21:06,240
What's up?

415
00:21:07,039 --> 00:21:08,559
He's going to the rescue center.

416
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:10,079
Yueyue told me.

417
00:21:10,519 --> 00:21:12,799
She said Ming Liang was asked to help

418
00:21:12,799 --> 00:21:14,799
take care of a little brown bear.

419
00:21:16,119 --> 00:21:17,519
I actually think

420
00:21:17,519 --> 00:21:19,319
those two kids now

421
00:21:20,640 --> 00:21:22,440
are getting closer and closer.

422
00:21:22,759 --> 00:21:23,400
Don't you think

423
00:21:24,119 --> 00:21:25,519
he's going to see Yueyue?

424
00:21:27,599 --> 00:21:29,039
What's with that look?

425
00:21:29,240 --> 00:21:30,480
He's going to the rescue center.

426
00:21:30,480 --> 00:21:31,839
If not Yueyue, who else?

427
00:21:33,079 --> 00:21:33,799
You look like

428
00:21:33,799 --> 00:21:35,799
you don't want us to be in-laws.

429
00:21:36,240 --> 00:21:37,039
That's not it.

430
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:40,799
Ming Liang.

431
00:21:41,799 --> 00:21:43,720
Remember to buy Yueyue

432
00:21:43,720 --> 00:21:45,039
her favorite milk tea.

433
00:21:45,039 --> 00:21:45,720
I know.

434
00:21:45,839 --> 00:21:47,200
She even gave me a snack list.

435
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:48,119
Asked me to buy everything on it.

436
00:21:49,079 --> 00:21:49,599
Alright, alright.

437
00:21:49,599 --> 00:21:50,319
Go on, hurry up.

438
00:21:50,640 --> 00:21:51,680
Mom, I'm heading out.

439
00:22:00,839 --> 00:22:01,519
Aisha.

440
00:22:01,839 --> 00:22:02,920
If we're free this afternoon,

441
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:04,440
let's go to the Grand Bazaar.

442
00:22:05,880 --> 00:22:07,480
If those two kids' feelings

443
00:22:07,559 --> 00:22:08,880
keep developing well,

444
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:10,480
they'll be engaged soon.

445
00:22:10,920 --> 00:22:12,839
We should dress up nicely too.

446
00:22:21,720 --> 00:22:22,279
Aisha.

447
00:22:23,279 --> 00:22:23,799
Look.

448
00:22:24,480 --> 00:22:25,599
That person is here again.

449
00:22:26,119 --> 00:22:27,279
Don't keep staring.

450
00:22:27,279 --> 00:22:28,000
It's rude.

451
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:28,559
No,

452
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:30,160
I just find it strange.

453
00:22:30,519 --> 00:22:31,960
Look at his clothes and accessories—

454
00:22:32,039 --> 00:22:33,440
he doesn't look like someone short on food.

455
00:22:34,119 --> 00:22:35,240
This person

456
00:22:36,160 --> 00:22:37,839
is different from the others before.

457
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:39,480
I just feel

458
00:22:39,759 --> 00:22:41,720
it's not that simple.

459
00:22:41,880 --> 00:22:43,440
So what do you think he does?

460
00:23:02,160 --> 00:23:03,039
He ate, he finally ate.

461
00:23:03,440 --> 00:23:04,519
Finally ate.

462
00:23:07,640 --> 00:23:08,599
Finally ate.

463
00:23:13,559 --> 00:23:14,880
I'm not a bad foster dad, right?

464
00:23:15,519 --> 00:23:16,480
Not bad.

465
00:23:19,359 --> 00:23:21,079
The little one finally has energy.

466
00:23:22,160 --> 00:23:23,359
Sorry to trouble you these days.

467
00:23:23,359 --> 00:23:24,559
You've had to come and go a lot.

468
00:23:25,240 --> 00:23:26,000
You say that

469
00:23:26,759 --> 00:23:28,079
but it's all for the bear cub.

470
00:23:28,599 --> 00:23:29,200
It's worth it.

471
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:30,400
Bear cub? Really?

472
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:31,559
Can't you call it something nicer?

473
00:23:32,799 --> 00:23:34,279
You haven't named it yet.

474
00:23:34,480 --> 00:23:35,720
Haven't had time.

475
00:23:37,160 --> 00:23:38,440
Why don't you name it?

476
00:23:38,519 --> 00:23:39,279
Me? Name it?

477
00:23:39,759 --> 00:23:41,319
You're basically its foster dad.

478
00:23:43,039 --> 00:23:43,559
Alright.

479
00:23:43,920 --> 00:23:44,799
Let me think.

480
00:23:45,720 --> 00:23:47,200
It suffered so much before.

481
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:50,200
I just hope it can be happy from now on.

482
00:23:51,359 --> 00:23:52,279
Let's call it Smiley.

483
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:53,599
What do you think?

484
00:23:54,240 --> 00:23:54,839
Smiley.

485
00:23:56,920 --> 00:23:57,599
That's nice.

486
00:24:01,319 --> 00:24:04,240
May it grow up healthy and happy.

487
00:24:05,359 --> 00:24:06,480
Alright, Smiley?

488
00:24:12,279 --> 00:24:13,119
Eat your meal like a good kid.

489
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:14,839
Grow up well.

490
00:24:15,160 --> 00:24:16,759
I'll come visit you often from now on.

491
00:24:20,240 --> 00:24:21,200
Why are you clicking your tongue?

492
00:24:21,720 --> 00:24:22,480
What's with that look?

493
00:24:22,559 --> 00:24:23,640
I... I... I...

494
00:24:23,759 --> 00:24:25,279
I don't know either.

495
00:24:25,279 --> 00:24:26,680
What kind of look should I have?

496
00:24:26,680 --> 00:24:28,240
You look like a cat with its tail pinched.

497
00:24:28,240 --> 00:24:29,000
What are you trying to say?

498
00:24:30,960 --> 00:24:31,480
Yueyue.

499
00:24:33,279 --> 00:24:34,720
He's your boyfriend.

500
00:24:35,200 --> 00:24:37,279
But now he's with Nana, the two of them...

501
00:24:37,519 --> 00:24:38,039
Uh...

502
00:24:40,119 --> 00:24:41,519
How many times have I told you?

503
00:24:41,519 --> 00:24:42,599
Stop bringing this up.

504
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:43,920
It's not just the restaurant—don't mention it.

505
00:24:43,920 --> 00:24:44,960
You can't talk about it here either.

506
00:24:46,279 --> 00:24:47,279
Maybe he doesn't even know...

507
00:24:47,279 --> 00:24:48,640
...he's your boyfriend, right?

508
00:24:49,920 --> 00:24:50,559
Hu Yue.

509
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:53,000
You're just crushing on him.

510
00:24:56,799 --> 00:24:57,599
He's my brother.

511
00:24:59,240 --> 00:25:00,480
My situation is way too complicated.

512
00:25:00,480 --> 00:25:01,440
Even if I explain, you won't get it.

513
00:25:01,680 --> 00:25:02,200
Uh... uh...

514
00:25:02,599 --> 00:25:04,279
That's a lot to take in.

515
00:25:04,680 --> 00:25:07,000
So... who is your boyfriend, then?

516
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:07,960
You're so annoying.

517
00:25:07,960 --> 00:25:08,559
Yueyue.

518
00:25:10,119 --> 00:25:11,079
Got yourself a boyfriend now.

519
00:25:13,960 --> 00:25:14,480
Who is it?

520
00:25:15,279 --> 00:25:17,359
Li Zhe said he'd set me up with someone.

521
00:25:19,720 --> 00:25:20,599
It's time to eat.

522
00:25:20,680 --> 00:25:22,079
Murat's Dad needs you more.

523
00:25:22,240 --> 00:25:22,759
Goodbye.

524
00:25:22,759 --> 00:25:23,599
Go see him off.

525
00:25:23,599 --> 00:25:24,599
Go, go, go.

526
00:25:24,640 --> 00:25:25,559
Let's go together.

527
00:25:25,799 --> 00:25:26,359
Take it slow.

528
00:25:26,359 --> 00:25:26,960
Goodbye.

529
00:25:29,559 --> 00:25:31,559
Did something happen to Murat's Dad?

530
00:25:32,559 --> 00:25:33,359
Nothing serious.

531
00:25:34,400 --> 00:25:36,359
You know, those who used to eat at the restaurant...

532
00:25:36,359 --> 00:25:37,079
Basically,

533
00:25:37,559 --> 00:25:39,720
they all came for Murat's Dad's cooking.

534
00:25:40,119 --> 00:25:42,240
Now there are lots of new customers.

535
00:25:42,359 --> 00:25:43,680
Most of them are young people.

536
00:25:44,039 --> 00:25:45,480
They're not used to his flavors.

537
00:25:45,839 --> 00:25:47,680
So he's a bit discouraged.

538
00:25:48,200 --> 00:25:50,119
A couple years ago, my dad's knee gave out.

539
00:25:50,519 --> 00:25:52,119
After he got a new one,

540
00:25:52,240 --> 00:25:53,440
for a while,

541
00:25:53,640 --> 00:25:55,119
he used to be so cheerful.

542
00:25:55,119 --> 00:25:56,240
But he got so down, he lost weight.

543
00:25:56,559 --> 00:25:58,319
So how did you deal with it?

544
00:25:58,359 --> 00:25:59,440
What could I do?

545
00:25:59,759 --> 00:26:00,599
As the younger generation,

546
00:26:00,599 --> 00:26:02,240
all we can do is be there for them.

547
00:26:02,319 --> 00:26:03,559
Just like when we were kids,

548
00:26:03,559 --> 00:26:05,079
they were always there for us.

549
00:26:05,559 --> 00:26:06,440
Don't worry.

550
00:26:06,759 --> 00:26:08,920
There's a saying we use at work.

551
00:26:09,319 --> 00:26:10,960
Every stage of life

552
00:26:11,039 --> 00:26:12,039
is a time to be an apprentice.

553
00:26:15,920 --> 00:26:16,319
I'm off.

554
00:26:24,359 --> 00:26:25,640
Potatoes, twenty kilos.

555
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:28,039
Tomatoes, let's get thirty kilos.

556
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:29,319
Okay.

557
00:26:29,319 --> 00:26:29,680
Oh, right.

558
00:26:30,079 --> 00:26:31,200
We need cheese too.

559
00:26:31,319 --> 00:26:32,599
We're almost out of blackcurrant.

560
00:26:33,279 --> 00:26:35,039
Didn't we just buy blackcurrant two days ago?

561
00:26:35,480 --> 00:26:36,000
Did you forget?

562
00:26:36,440 --> 00:26:37,359
My Blackcurrant Naan

563
00:26:37,359 --> 00:26:38,759
is our restaurant's signature now.

564
00:26:38,839 --> 00:26:40,039
Every table ordered it today.

565
00:26:40,440 --> 00:26:41,839
Several people even took it to go.

566
00:26:42,279 --> 00:26:43,559
Look at you, so impressive.

567
00:26:46,880 --> 00:26:48,039
Blackcurrant.

568
00:26:49,599 --> 00:26:50,480
Murat's Dad.

569
00:26:51,759 --> 00:26:52,799
That's enough, enough, enough.

570
00:26:56,279 --> 00:26:57,000
Almost forgot.

571
00:26:57,799 --> 00:26:58,480
Flour.

572
00:26:58,559 --> 00:26:59,599
The most important—flour.

573
00:27:00,240 --> 00:27:02,000
We used to go through a month's flour supply.

574
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:03,119
Now we've used it all in just a few days.

575
00:27:04,279 --> 00:27:06,160
